lass=3D"schema-faq-question">How do I handle seasonal working-capital swing=
s?</strong> <p class=3D"schema-faq-answer">Use <strong>quarterly</strong> p=
rojections or a <strong>13-week cash-flow</strong> for WC-intensive or seas=
onal businesses. Translate <strong>AR/Inv/AP days</strong> into dollar bala=
nces, and model the <strong>revolver/ABL</strong> dynamically with a facili=
ty cap and borrowing base where relevant.</p> </div> <div class=3D"schema-f=
aq-section" id=3D"faq-question-1756768318339"><strong class=3D"schema-faq-q=
uestion">What exit multiples should I assume?</strong> <p class=3D"schema-f=
aq-answer">Start with <strong>entry multiple</strong>, then test <strong>=
=C2=B11.0=C3=97</strong> to bracket valuation risk. Tie expansion/compressi=
on to specific factors (mix shift, growth durability, margin/quality improv=
ements, public comp cycles). Avoid assuming expansion without a <strong>val=
ue-creation thesis</strong>.</p> </div> <div class=3D"schema-faq-section" i=
d=3D"faq-question-1756768329494"><strong class=3D"schema-faq-question">How =
detailed should my debt schedule be?</strong> <p class=3D"schema-faq-answer=
">Model <strong>each tranche</strong>: base rate + spread, amortization, <s=
trong>mandatory vs. optional prepayments</strong>, <strong>cash-sweep % aft=
er a minimum liquidity buffer</strong>, and <strong>covenant tests</strong>=
 (leverage, interest coverage). Calculate interest on <strong>BoP or averag=
e balances</strong> to avoid circularity.</p> </div> <div class=3D"schema-f=
aq-section" id=3D"faq-question-1756768340675"><strong class=3D"schema-faq-q=
uestion">What if my model shows covenant breaches?</strong> <p class=3D"sch=
ema-faq-answer">Reflect a real <strong>amend-and-extend path</strong>: amen=
dment fees, margin step-ups, tighter baskets, potential <strong>PIK toggles=
</strong> on junior paper, <strong>equity cure</strong>, cost-out plan, and=
 (often) a <strong>longer hold</strong>. Make each change explicit so retur=
ns reconcile.</p> </div> <div class=3D"schema-faq-section" id=3D"faq-questi=
on-1756768352687"><strong class=3D"schema-faq-question">Should I model bolt=
-on acquisitions?</strong> <p class=3D"schema-faq-answer">Only if they=E2=
=80=99re <strong>central to the thesis</strong>. If included, model timing =
(close date), purchase price allocation, <strong>integration costs</strong>=
, incremental <strong>=CE=94NWC</strong>, and synergy timing (revenue/cost)=
. Otherwise, keep the base case <strong>organic</strong> and show bolt-ons =
as upside.</p> </div> </div>



